"1243","1287":"1287","1319":"1319","Vayres, Libourne, Gironde, Nouvelle-Aquitaine, France":"Vayres, Gironde, Nouvelle-Aquitaine, France","France":"France","Dax, Landes, Nouvelle-Aquitaine, France":"Dax, Landes, Aquitaine, France","nameMeanings":[{"name":"de","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Dilip, Anirban, Gopal, Alok, Anindya, Arunava, Asit, Asok, Dibyendu, Goutam, Indra, Indranil.","Indian: variant of   Dey  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Dey","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Ashit, Indu, Naina, Partha, Soumya, Ajit, Anjan, Anjana, Anup, Arjun, Arun, Ashim.","English, Scottish, and Welsh: variant of   Day  .","German: topographic name from a field name in North Rhine-Westphalia, denoting a sizeable piece of land, from Middle Low German <i>dē</i> ‘thigh’ (referring to the shape of the property)."]}]},{"name":"Bourg","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  French Camille, Antoine, Cecile, Emile, Alcide, Anatole, Clovis, Ferrel, Leonce, Onile.","French: topographic name for someone who lived in a town as opposed to one who lived in a village, from Middle French <i>bourg</i> (Old French <i>burc</i>) ‘fortified town’, or a habitational name from (Le) Bourg, the name of several places in various parts of France. Compare   Bourke  ,   Bourque  ,   Burk  , and   Burke  .","History: Antoine Bourg/Bourque from Martaizé in Vienne, France, married Antoinette Landry in Acadia <i>c.</i> 1642. His descendants also bear altered forms of the surname, such as <i>Bourke</i>, <i>Bourque</i>, and <i>Burk(e)</i>."],"variants":[{"name":"Bourgeois","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  French Andre, Marcel, Emile, Alphonse, Armand, Camille, Gaston, Monique, Pierre, Lucien, Michel, Normand.","French: from <i>bourgeois</i> ‘burgher’ (from Old French <i>burgeis</i>, from <i>burc</i> ‘fortified town’), a status name for an inhabitant and (usually) freeman of a fortified town (see   Bourg  ). Compare   Lebourgeois   and also   Boss  ,   Burgess  , and   Bushway  .","History: Jacques Bourgeois from France married Jeanne Trahan in Acadia <i>c.</i> 1643. Pierre Bourgeois from Poligny in Jura, France, married Marie-Louise Cléroux in Saint-Vincent-de-Paul, QC, in 1753."]},{"name":"Bourke","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Irish Brendan, Dermot, Liam, Murphy.","Irish: variant of   Burke  .","Americanized form of French   Bourg   or of its altered form   Bourque  ."]},{"name":"Bourget","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  French Normand, Jacques, Lucien, Pierre, Aime, Andre, Fernand, Germaine, Laurent, Ludger, Marcel, Marcell.","French: topographic name, a diminutive of   Bourg  , or a habitational name from (Le) Bourget, the name of several places in various parts of France.","Altered form of French <b>Bourgeais</b>, a variant of   Bourgeois  ."]},{"name":"Boulerice","meanings":["Altered form of Breton <b>Bourhis</b>: from <i>bourc'his</i> ‘burgher’, a status name for an inhabitant and (usually) freeman of a fortified town (see   Bourg  , compare   Bourgeois  )."]},{"name":"Bourque","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  French Armand, Lucien, Pierre, Andre, Aurele, Camille, Emile, Fernand, Henri, Jacques, Marcel, Normand.","French (mainly Doubs): variant of   Bourg   and, in North America, (also) an altered form of this.","History: The (majority of the) American bearers of the surname <i>Bourque</i> are descendants of Antoine Bourg/Bourque from France (see   Bourg  )."]}]},{"name":"Guitard","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  French Jean-Pierre, Laurent, Leandre, Patrice.  German Waltraud.","French:","from the ancient Germanic personal name <i>Widhard</i>, composed of the elements <i>wid(u)</i> ‘wood, forest’ and <i>hard</i> ‘hard, strong’."],"variants":[{"name":"Guitar","meanings":["French: variant of   Guitard   and, in North America, (also) an altered form of this. The surname <i>Guitar</i> has apparently died out in France."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Guitard de Bourg was born about 1240, in Dax, Landes, Nouvelle-Aquitaine, France, his father, Jean DE BOURG, was 31 and his mother, Rose deVertheuil, was 26. He married Thomasse Gombaut De Veyres in 1257, in Vayres, Gironde, Nouvelle-Aquitaine, France. They were the parents of at least 2 daughters. He died on 6 June 1287, at the age of 48."},"et":{"Abt 1240–6 JUN 1287":"umbes 1240–6. juuni 1287","1240–1287":"1240–1287","1243–1285":"1243–1285","1257–Female":"1257–Surnud","1268–1319":"1268–1319","1210–1254":"1210–1254","1215–Female":"1215–Surnud","12 January 1254":"12. jaanuar 1254","1285":"1285","1240":"1240","6 JUN 1287":"6. juuni 1287","Abt 1240":"umbes 1240","1215":"1215","1257":"1257","1268":"1268","1235":"1235","1254":"1254","1210":"1210","1243":"1243","1287":"1287","1319":"1319","Vayres, Libourne, Gironde, Nouvelle-Aquitaine, France":"Vayres, Gironde, Nouvelle-Aquitaine, Prantsusmaa","France":"Prantsusmaa","Dax, Landes, Nouvelle-Aquitaine, France":"Dax, Landes, Aquitaine, Prantsusmaa"},"fi":{"Abt 1240–6 JUN 1287":"noin 1240–6. kesäkuuta 1287","1240–1287":"1240–1287","1243–1285":"1243–1285","1257–Female":"1257–Kuollut","1268–1319":"1268–1319","1210–1254":"1210–1254","1215–Female":"1215–Kuollut","12 January 1254":"12. tammikuuta 1254","1285":"1285","1240":"1240","6 JUN 1287":"6. kesäkuuta 1287","Abt 1240":"noin 1240","1215":"1215","1257":"1257","1268":"1268","1235":"1235","1254":"1254","1210":"1210","1243":"1243","1287":"1287","1319":"1319","Vayres, Libourne, Gironde, Nouvelle-Aquitaine, France":"Vayres, Gironde, Nouvelle-Aquitaine, Ranska","France":"Ranska","Dax, Landes, Nouvelle-Aquitaine, France":"Dax, Landes, Aquitaine, Ranska"},"fr":{"Abt 1240–6 JUN 1287":"environ 1240–6 juin 1287","1240–1287":"1240–1287","12